Description: Large seal-impression made of clay. The front is slightly curved following one of the rear sides which looks like it was attached to a large curved object like a storage vessel or vat (diameter 60cm or more), the second rear side is flat. The front shows a large impression in the shape of an oval with hieroglyphs inside (dwA/sbA (tjt?...) n kAS). Traces from smearing while still wet surface. Originally broken into two pieces, now glued together.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
